						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in a field called <hi rend="italic">dēvasva.</hi></p>						

						<p>Virūpāksha, 1476 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1398, Du[rmukha], Bhādrapada śu. 2, Wednesday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1476 A.D., August 21.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to register certain gifts for woship and offerings in the temple of Mahādēva Basarūru (?) by <hi rend="italic">mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Viṭharasa-oḍeya</hi> who was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi> All other details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
